'''Autotoky''' is uniparental reproduction by [[self-fertilization]] or by [[parthenogenesis]].<ref name=Thorp>{{Cite book| publisher = Academic Press| isbn = 978-0-12-374855-3| last = Thorp| first = James H.| title = Ecology and Classification of North American Freshwater Invertebrates| date = 2009-11-24}}</ref><ref name=Perry>{{Cite book| publisher = CABI| isbn = 978-1-84593-056-1| last = Perry| first = Roland N.|author2= Maurice Moens| title = Plant nematology| date = 2006-08-10}}</ref> The word comes from the Greek words ''auto'' meaning self and ''tokos'' meaning birth.

