'''''How to Survive Anything, Anywhere: A Handbook of Survival Skills for Every Scenario and Environment''''' is a book written by [[Chris McNab (historian)|Chris McNab]]. The diverse themes covered relate to [[survivalism]] and include topics such as: first-aid, shelter, hunting and fishing, self-defense, weather, tools, etc. It contains illustrations.<ref>''How to Survive Anything, Anywhere: A Handbook of Survival Skills for Every Scenario and Environment'', {{ISBN|978-0071440530}} First Edition 2004</ref><ref>''Cómo sobrevivir a cualquier cosa en cualquier lugar'', {{ISBN|978-968-13-4196-1}}, Editorial Diana S.A. de C.V. Mexico 2008</ref>

